---
description: Core rules for omero-zarr-C parity porting
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

- Start with `AGENTS.md`, including its pinned Karpathy agent baseline.
- Never modify `source_code_v.0.15.0/`.
- Port one upstream surface at a time.
- Keep C ABI wrappers thin and preserve upstream behavior first.
- Do not add Python-object, pybind, or embedded-interpreter semantics to C++.
- Add differential tests for every port.
- Benchmark before claiming performance gains.
